Condition.name: Fnd0AssignTaskPrivilege
Condition.expression: (u.group_name="*") OR (task != NULL AND ((task.owning_user=u.user) OR (task.fnd0Assignee=u.user) OR (task.active_surrogate=u.user))) OR (signoff != NULL AND (signoff.decision=0) AND ((signoff.fnd0ParentTask.owning_user=u.user) OR ((signoff.group_member != NULL) AND (signoff.group_member.user=u.user)) OR ((signoff.active_surrogate != NULL) AND (signoff.active_surrogate.user=u.user))))
Condition.description: This condition "Fnd0AssignTaskPrivilege" restricts the assignment of workflow task as follows. If the current user's group is dba, no further checks are made. For single user tasks the current user must be either an assignee or an active surrogate for the task. For signoff tasks the decision must not be set and the current user must be either the assigned group member or the active surrogate. Modified OOTB (u.group_name="dba") as (u.group_name="*") for TDPS .
